comments.body:
Joe: This is the new code you added last night :

    // Multiple extents; merge them into a single contiguous buffer
    avifRWDataRealloc(&item->mergedExtents, item->size);

In avifParseItemLocationBox(), the += operation in the following code needs to guard against overflowing the uint32_t sum:

            avifDecoderItemExtent * extent = (avifDecoderItemExtent *)avifArrayPushPtr(&item->extents);
            extent->offset = (uint32_t)(baseOffset + extentOffset);
            extent->size = (uint32_t)extentLength;
            item->size += extent->size;

At this point, extent->offset and extent->size have not been validated. We do that in avifDecoderDataCalcItemPtr():

    // Multiple extents; merge them into a single contiguous buffer
    avifRWDataRealloc(&item->mergedExtents, item->size);
    uint8_t * front = item->mergedExtents.data;
    size_t remainingBytes = item->mergedExtents.size;
    for (uint32_t extentIter = 0; extentIter < item->extents.count; ++extentIter) {
        avifDecoderItemExtent * extent = &item->extents.extent[extentIter];
        if (extent->offset > offsetBuffer->size) {
            return NULL;
        }
        uint64_t offsetSize = (uint64_t)extent->offset + (uint64_t)extent->size;
        if (offsetSize > (uint64_t)offsetBuffer->size) {
            return NULL;
        }
        if ((size_t)extent->size > remainingBytes) {
            return NULL;
        }

        memcpy(front, offsetBuffer->data + extent->offset, extent->size);
        front += extent->size;
        remainingBytes -= extent->size;
    }

There are several ways to deal with this bug. One thing we may want to do is to impose a maximum on item size. Right now we only have a maximum on image size, which is related but different. This alone should fix the out-of-memory error.

Then, we can split the above code in avifDecoderDataCalcItemPtr() into three steps:

1. A for loop that validates all the extent->offset and extent->size.
2. Having validated all the extent->offset and extent->size, allocate the single contiguous buffer:
    avifRWDataRealloc(&item->mergedExtents, item->size);
3. A for loop that copies all extents from offsetBuffer to item->mergedExtents.
